Iran and  Armenia  agreed to build a
hydroelectric power plant on the Aras river, which borders the
two nations,  Press TV  reported, without saying where it got the
information.  Iran and Armenia agreed on June 2 to start construction in
August of the Meghri power plant, which will have the capacity
to produce 130 megawatts of electricity, the Iranian state-run
news channel said. It didnâ€™t provide financial details for the
